 Пример книжки на русском в bookdown Борис Демешев 2019-03-12 Глава 1 Введение После русских названий глав метка {#label} обязательна! В yaml заголовок index.Rmd добавлено lang: ru-RU otherlangs: en-GB mainfont: &quot;Linux Libertine O&quot; monofont: &quot;Linux Libertine O&quot; sansfont: &quot;Linux Libertine O&quot; В _bookdown.yml добавлено output_dir: docs и chapter_name исправлено на “Глава” Некоторые плагины Firefox могут блокировать рендеринг математических формул при публикации книжки на github. Например, в Privacy Badger нужно разблокировать mathjax.rstudio.com. В preamble.tex добавлено: % why do we need 
ewfontfamily: % http://tex.stackexchange.com/questions/91507/ 
ewfontfamily{\cyrillicfonttt}{Linux Libertine O} 
ewfontfamily{\cyrillicfont}{Linux Libertine O} 
ewfontfamily{\cyrillicfontsf}{Linux Libertine O} Далее полезные хвосты из исходного примера: # automatically create a bib database for R packages knitr::write_bib(c( .packages(), &#39;bookdown&#39;, &#39;knitr&#39;, &#39;rmarkdown&#39; ), &#39;packages.bib&#39;) You can label chapter and section titles using {#label} after them, e.g., we can reference Chapter 1. If you do not manually label them, there will be automatic labels anyway, e.g., Chapter ??. Figures and tables with captions will be placed in figure and table environments, respectively. par(mar = c(4, 4, .1, .1)) plot(pressure, type = &#39;b&#39;, pch = 19) Figure 1.1: Here is a nice figure! Reference a figure by its code chunk label with the fig: prefix, e.g., see Figure 1.1. Similarly, you can reference tables generated from knitr::kable(), e.g., see Table 1.1. knitr::kable( head(iris, 20), caption = &#39;Here is a nice table!&#39;, booktabs = TRUE ) Table 1.1: Here is a nice table! Sepal.Length Sepal.Width Petal.Length Petal.Width Species 5.1 3.5 1.4 0.2 setosa 4.9 3.0 1.4 0.2 setosa 4.7 3.2 1.3 0.2 setosa 4.6 3.1 1.5 0.2 setosa 5.0 3.6 1.4 0.2 setosa 5.4 3.9 1.7 0.4 setosa 4.6 3.4 1.4 0.3 setosa 5.0 3.4 1.5 0.2 setosa 4.4 2.9 1.4 0.2 setosa 4.9 3.1 1.5 0.1 setosa 5.4 3.7 1.5 0.2 setosa 4.8 3.4 1.6 0.2 setosa 4.8 3.0 1.4 0.1 setosa 4.3 3.0 1.1 0.1 setosa 5.8 4.0 1.2 0.2 setosa 5.7 4.4 1.5 0.4 setosa 5.4 3.9 1.3 0.4 setosa 5.1 3.5 1.4 0.3 setosa 5.7 3.8 1.7 0.3 setosa 5.1 3.8 1.5 0.3 setosa You can write citations, too. For example, we are using the bookdown package (Xie 2018) in this sample book, which was built on top of R Markdown and knitr (Xie 2015).
